---
/* Static shell for the persistent left/right active-match rails (URS-120…
   URS-128). All dynamic content is filled in by src/live/rails.ts at runtime
   -- this file carries no business logic (project convention). Both <aside>s
   start empty/hidden (inline `display:none` set here matches the JS default
   of "zero live matches") so there's no flash of an empty rail before the
   first poll resolves (URS-124). CSS breakpoint (live.css, URS-125/URS-126)
   hides these entirely below RAILS_MIN_WIDTH_PX and shows the existing
   "Live now" panel instead -- one live UI per breakpoint, never both. */
---

<aside
  id="rail-left"
  class="rail rail-left"
  aria-label="Live matches, left of draw"
  style="display:none"
>
</aside>
<aside
  id="rail-right"
  class="rail rail-right"
  aria-label="Live matches, right of draw"
  style="display:none"
>
</aside>
